From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 11:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add the GRX-012 taa_resolve recording-smoke and gated real-pass

 opt-in arms with result writeback scaffold

Stacked on 0001..0018. This is the GRX-012 bridge-recording / real-pass
opt-in slice (the GRX-009 0008+0009+0010 layers merged into one patch for
the taa_resolve pass), mirroring GRX-011 0016. It is a bring-up gate, not a
default enablement, and it does not change the shipping fallback semantics.

- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: adds three per-pass opt-in
  settings that all default to false and are separate from
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/enabled:
  .../taa_resolve/dispatch_recording_smoke, .../taa_resolve/dispatch_real_pass,
  and .../taa_resolve/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h: declares the reserved taa_resolve
  real-pass arm flag RXGD_CAP_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS (bridge value 1 << 6)
  carried in RxGdCaps.flags. This reuses the existing flags field: the C
  ABI struct layout and RXGD_ABI_VERSION are unchanged.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp: try_create_session() sets
  RXGD_CAP_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS ONLY when the taa_resolve dispatch_real_pass
  opt-in is enabled, and clears RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64 ONLY when the
  harness-only taa_resolve real_pass_force_capability_downgrade knob is
  enabled. try_record_taa_resolve() emits RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS
  only on the real-pass arm OK path and RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_RECORD
  on the same OK path; both markers are gated under the harness-only
  dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in (GRX Wave 4 print gating below).
- render_forward_clustered.cpp TAA branch: when try_record_taa_resolve()
  returned true on the real-pass arm, the bridge dispatched the resolve kernel
  into the real taa/temp destination ID3D12Resource*, so the single-view
  resolve subset result is physically written into the temp buffer. The result
  writeback SCAFFOLD prints RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK,
  then clears the flag so the FULL native Godot taa->process still runs as the
  continuation/backstop (the kernel covers only one view with no history
  double-buffer copy-back; GPU math parity is still pending measurement).

GRX Wave 4 print-gating revision (patch number unchanged, PATCH_ALLOCATION.md
section 4 rule 2): the per-dispatch RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS
module marker and the call-site
RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK scaffold marker are
harness instrumentation and are now printed ONLY under the harness-only
dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in, so the production dispatch_real_pass opt-in
path emits zero per-dispatch stdout (pass engagement is read from the shim
engagement counter file / RXGD_SUMMARY instead). Semantics are otherwise
unchanged.

The bridge fails closed on the real-pass arm and returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK
with a machine-readable RXGD_TAA_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming the
FIRST missing prerequisite; the real dispatch is only linked under the
test-only d3d12-recording-shim bridge feature. This does not change
RXGD_ABI_VERSION, does not enable the pass by default (all four taa_resolve
per-pass settings still default to false), does not flip real_gpu_pass to
true by itself, and makes no visual, measured-telemetry, GPU-timestamp, or
performance claim by itself.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index 15de768..299f2ca 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -132,6 +132,35 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK for RXGD_PASS_TAA_RESOLVE, so the native TAA
 	// resolve keeps rendering in practice and no acceleration is claimed.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/enabled", false);
+	// GRX-012: harness-only Godot-runtime taa_resolve bridge dispatch
+	// recording smoke opt-in (0008-level). Defaults to false so the
+	// shipping build never arms the recording-smoke marker path. It only
+	// gates the module-side RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_RECORD marker; the
+	// bridge record path itself is only linked when the loaded
+	// rurix_godot.dll is built with the test-only d3d12-recording-shim
+	// feature AND the dispatch_real_pass opt-in below armed the fail-closed
+	// real-pass gate.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_recording_smoke", false);
+	// GRX-012: opt-in gated REAL taa_resolve pass bring-up arm (0009-level).
+	// Defaults to false so the shipping build never arms the real-pass
+	// attempt. Even when enabled the bridge runs its runtime binding
+	// preflight, dispatch eligibility, per-slot kernel-binding-kind
+	// conformance, and math-parity checks and keeps returning
+	// RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK (with a machine-readable
+	// RXGD_TAA_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED diagnostic naming the first missing
+	// prerequisite) unless every check passes AND a runtime-mappable real
+	// dispatch path is linked (d3d12-recording-shim builds only); the
+	// shipping feature-off bridge fails closed with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked, so the native TAA resolve keeps rendering.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_real_pass", false);
+	// GRX-012: harness-only forced-failure knob for the taa_resolve fallback
+	// red/green leg (0009-level template of the luminance
+	// real_pass_force_capability_downgrade). When enabled the module clears
+	// the shader-int64 capability it advertises to the bridge, so the
+	// bridge taa_resolve preflight fails closed with unsupported_device while
+	// the native Godot TAA resolve path keeps rendering. Defaults to false;
+	// never enabled by the shipping build/config.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade", false);
 
 #if defined(D3D12_ENABLED)
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/enabled")) {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index e07469c..8b7fa51 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -251,6 +251,23 @@ void RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_create_session() {
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/ssao_blur/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
 		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
 	}
+	// GRX-012: arm the opt-in gated REAL taa_resolve pass attempt ONLY when
+	// the default-false taa_resolve dispatch_real_pass opt-in is enabled. The
+	// bridge still fails closed (fallback + RXGD_TAA_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
+	// first missing prerequisite) unless every gate passes AND the
+	// d3d12-recording-shim real dispatch path is linked and completes; this
+	// is a bring-up gate, not a default runtime pass.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_real_pass")) {
+		caps.flags |= RXGD_CAP_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS;
+	}
+	// GRX-012: harness-only taa_resolve forced-failure knob. Clearing the
+	// shader-int64 capability makes the bridge taa_resolve preflight fail
+	// closed with unsupported_device while the native Godot TAA resolve path
+	// keeps rendering; the fallback red/green leg of the GRX-012 real-pass
+	// enablement smoke verifies exactly this.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/real_pass_force_capability_downgrade")) {
+		caps.flags &= ~RXGD_CAP_SHADER_INT64;
+	}
 	if (adapter_luid_valid) {
 		memcpy(caps.adapter_luid, &adapter_luid, sizeof(adapter_luid));
 	}
@@ -682,6 +699,22 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_taa_resolve(uint64_t p_color_native_handle
 		}
 		return false;
 	}
+	// GRX-012: only reachable when the bridge's opt-in real-pass arm actually
+	// returned RXGD_STATUS_OK after a real recorded dispatch (d3d12-recording-
+	// shim builds only; the shipping feature-off bridge always falls back with
+	// real_dispatch_path_not_linked first). GRX Wave 4 print gating: both
+	// per-dispatch stdout markers are harness instrumentation and are gated
+	// under the harness-only dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in — the production
+	// dispatch_real_pass path emits zero per-dispatch stdout (pass engagement
+	// is read from the shim engagement counter file / RXGD_SUMMARY instead).
+	// The REAL_PASS marker still reports the real-pass arm; the RECORD marker
+	// remains the recording-smoke marker.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS: pass=RXGD_PASS_TAA_RESOLVE dispatched=1");
+	}
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_TAA_RESOLVE recorded=1");
+	}
 	return true;
 }
 
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
index ccb3cd0..b338d01 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h
@@ -55,6 +55,16 @@
 // diagnostic unless every check passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real
 // dispatch path is linked and completes.
 #define RXGD_CAP_SSAO_BLUR_REAL_PASS 32u
+// GRX-012 opt-in taa_resolve real-pass arm carried in RxGdCaps.flags (ABI
+// v1, no struct layout change; bridge value 1 << 6). Set only when the
+// default-false rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_real_pass
+// opt-in is enabled. Setting it never on its own makes the bridge return
+// RXGD_STATUS_OK: the fail-closed TaaResolveGate runs preflight ->
+// eligibility -> binding-kind -> math-parity -> linked-dispatch checks and
+// returns RXGD_STATUS_FALLBACK with an RXGD_TAA_REAL_PASS_BLOCKED
+// diagnostic unless every check passes AND the d3d12-recording-shim real
+// dispatch path is linked and completes.
+#define RXGD_CAP_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS 64u
 
 typedef struct RxGdCaps {
 	uint32_t abi_version;
diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.cpp
index 363a047..a109970 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.cpp
@@ -2551,6 +2551,27 @@ void RenderForwardClustered::_render_scene(RenderDataRD *p_render_data, const Co
 					const float rurix_taa_disocclusion = 2.5f;
 					const float rurix_taa_variance = CLAMP(1.1f * (1080.0f / (float)MAX(rurix_taa_size.y, 1)), 0.75f, 1.0f);
 					rurix_recorded_taa_resolve = D3D12Hooks::get_singleton()->try_record_taa_resolve(rurix_taa_color_handle, rurix_taa_depth_handle, rurix_taa_velocity_handle, rurix_taa_prev_velocity_handle, rurix_taa_history_handle, rurix_taa_temp_handle, (uint32_t)MAX(rurix_taa_size.x, 0), (uint32_t)MAX(rurix_taa_size.y, 0), rurix_taa_disocclusion, rurix_taa_variance);
+					if (rurix_recorded_taa_resolve) {
+						// GRX-012 result writeback SCAFFOLD (0010-level). The Rurix
+						// bridge dispatched the full-resolution TAA resolve kernel
+						// into the real taa/temp destination ID3D12Resource*, so the
+						// single-view resolve subset result is physically written into
+						// the temp buffer. Record that writeback with a machine-
+						// readable marker, then keep the FULL native Godot taa->process
+						// as the continuation/backstop: the kernel covers only one view
+						// with no history double-buffer copy-back or prev_velocity
+						// bookkeeping (taa.cpp copy_to_rect x3 per frame), and GPU math
+						// parity is still pending measurement, so the native
+						// taa->process re-resolves every view and the image can never
+						// change while this scaffold is in place.
+						// GRX Wave 4 print gating: harness instrumentation only
+						// (dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in); zero per-dispatch
+						// stdout on the production path.
+						if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/taa_resolve/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+							print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_TAA_RESOLVE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK: dst=taa_temp native_continuation=active scaffold=1");
+						}
+						rurix_recorded_taa_resolve = false;
+					}
 				}
 			}
 #endif
-- 
